# Where should a drinks company run promotions?

## ðŸ“– Background
Your company owns a chain of stores across Russia that sell a variety of alcoholic drinks. 
The company recently ran a wine promotion in Saint Petersburg that was very successful.
Due to the cost to the business, it isnâ€™t possible to run the promotion in all regions. 
The marketing team would like to target 10 other regions that have similar buying habits to Saint Petersburg where they would expect the promotion to be similarly successful.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

import pandas as pd
df = pd.read_csv(r'./data/russian_alcohol_consumption.csv')
df = pd.DataFrame(df).dropna() # reduced from 1615 to 1549 columns
head= df.head() #year     region  wine  beer  vodka  champagne  brandy


wine=df.groupby(["region"])[['wine']].mean().sort_values(by=['wine'], ascending=False).round(2).iloc[:10]
beer=df.groupby(["region"])[['beer']].mean().sort_values(by=['beer'], ascending=False).round(2).iloc[:10]
vodka=df.groupby(["region"])[['vodka']].mean().sort_values(by=['vodka'], ascending=False).round(2).iloc[:10]
brandy=df.groupby(["region"])[['brandy']].mean().sort_values(by=['brandy'], ascending=False).round(2).iloc[:10]
print(brandy)
